                     <interp inst="t18310407-72-person687" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Messrs. Young and Luxmore, pawnbrokers, in St. Martin's-lane. I have an eight-day dial, which I took in pawn on the 17th of March, of the prisoner, about seven o'clock in the evening; I lent 1l. 10s. on it - I asked where he got it; he said he had made it for Mr. Stiles, whose name was upon it, but he was not within, and he would take it out again when he was within - I have not the least doubt of the prisoner's person; this is the counterpart of the duplicate I gave him.</p>
               <p>
            
